Rating: 3
This is a very tasty breakfast cake but I found it very fragile and easy to fall apart. This can cause problems in the mornings with sleepy heads. Instead of baking it in a bundt pan, I poured it into a large loaf pan to facilitate removal and cutting but still had trouble with its delicacy.

Rating: 4
Wonderful!! My guests raved about this very moist and tender breakfast cake. I served it for brunch. A glaze of orange juice, butter, a dash of salt, and powdered sugar over the warm cake added a lot of extra flavor. This cake is in my recipe box and on my favorite list.

Rating: 3
I have been making this cake ever since I read the recipe in 1996. It is great with coffee at breakfast or in the afternoon. I use Craisins and put the topping in between two layers of the batter for a nice swirl effect. I found it didn't want to stick to the top. The buttermilk really makes this a special cake.

